answerText: Carhenge[10] Carhenge should not be confused with the sort of similar "Cadillac Ranch" art installation located in this state's city of Amarillo.

subject: Geography
question: Question: This location was built by Jim Reinders and dedicated at the 1987 summer solstice. [10] Name this tourist destination found near Alliance, Nebraska. It is a replica of the English Stonehenge, except it uses mechanical materials which are covered with gray spray paint.
